      "writtenOn": "2026-07-13T08:35:45Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Run keyword used for openssl — replace with Run Process\n\nRun (OperatingSystem library) is deprecated in favour of Run Process (Process library). Additionally, passing the entire command as a single space-separated string is fragile when paths contain spaces.\n\n\n```\n${result}\u003d  Run Process\n...  openssl  dgst  -sha256  -verify  ${fw_verify_dir}/publickey\n...  -signature  ${fw_verify_dir}/${image}.sig  ${fw_verify_dir}/${image}\nShould Contain  ${result.stdout}  Verified OK\n...  msg\u003d${image} signature verification failed: ${result.stdout}\n```\n\nRun Process with individual arguments is immune to shell word-splitting on paths with spaces and captures both stdout and stderr for better diagnostics.",
      "revId": "82b61dd4e89794a7198981fc6cb8f841261555b7",
      "serverId": "adbd0a64-1f21-4d83-b585-671fe73cb6e4"
    },
